---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About - USCitizenship2032" description="Who is behind USCitizenship2032 and why this project exists.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-dark py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container text-center max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-warm-white mb-6">About This Project</h1>
      <p class="text-warm-white/80 text-lg">
        A personal project by an American who got tired of the shouting match.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Story -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Why I Started This</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-warm-gray leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          My name is JT Turner. I am not a politician, a lobbyist, or an immigration lawyer. I am an American who has been watching the birthright citizenship debate for years and kept waiting for someone to suggest something that actually makes sense.
        </p>

        <p>
          The conversation is stuck. One side says do not touch the 14th Amendment. The other side tries to rewrite it through executive orders that get struck down in court. Meanwhile, real families live with uncertainty, and the public loses trust in a system that feels like it was built for a different time.
        </p>

        <p>
          So I looked at what the rest of the world does. And I found something surprising: the U.S. is an extreme outlier. The large majority of developed countries, including the ones Americans on both sides admire most, do not do unconditional birthright citizenship.
        </p>

        <p>
          The UK changed in 1983. Ireland changed in 2004. India changed step by step through 1986, 2003, and 2019. Every Nordic country uses descent-only. Japan, Switzerland, South Korea all require a citizen parent. And Australia has a 10-year path that is almost the same as what I am proposing.
        </p>

        <p>
          This is not radical. It is normal. The U.S. just has not caught up yet.
        </p>

        <p class="font-semibold text-near-black">
          So I wrote it down. Not as an opinion piece. Not as a tweet. As an actual proposed amendment with real sections, real rules, and a real timeline. And then I built this site to share it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="bg-teal-50 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What This Project Is (and Is Not)</h2>

      <div class="grid gap-6">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-xl font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">A personal project</h3>
            <p class="text-warm-gray">This is not connected to any political party, think tank, PAC, or organization. It is one person trying to put a better idea out into the world.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-xl font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Based on facts, not opinions</h3>
            <p class="text-warm-gray">Every claim on this site links to actual laws and real data. The <a href="/comparison">30-country comparison</a> includes direct links to each country's legal text. Check the sources yourself.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-xl font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Open to criticism</h3>
            <p class="text-warm-gray">The amendment text is a draft. It has tough questions that still need answers. It needs legal review. The full project is <a href="https://github.com/jtwebman/uscitizenship2032" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">on GitHub</a> so lawyers, experts, and regular people can test every word. The best version will be written by many people, not just one.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-xl font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">&times;</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Not anti-immigrant</h3>
            <p class="text-warm-gray">This proposal does not reduce immigration, deport anyone, or remove any existing path to citizenship. It updates how birthright works, the same way the UK, Australia, and Germany already have.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-teal-600 text-xl font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">&times;</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Not a campaign</h3>
            <p class="text-warm-gray">There is no donation button. No merchandise. No candidate. This is an idea, laid out clearly, with evidence. If it is good enough, it will gain support on its own.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What's Next -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What Comes Next</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-gold-500 text-white font-bold text-sm shrink-0">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Get the idea out there</h3>
            <p class="text-warm-gray">Share this site. Send it to someone you disagree with. If the idea holds up when both sides look at it, it is worth pushing forward.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-gold-500 text-white font-bold text-sm shrink-0">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Open up the amendment text</h3>
            <p class="text-warm-gray">The draft is already <a href="https://github.com/jtwebman/uscitizenship2032" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">on GitHub</a> for public review. Lawyers, immigration experts, and everyday citizens can <a href="https://github.com/jtwebman/uscitizenship2032/issues/new/choose" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">open an issue</a> to suggest changes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-gold-500 text-white font-bold text-sm shrink-0">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Build a coalition</h3>
            <p class="text-warm-gray">Find people on the left, right, and center who agree the current system is broken and that a constitutional fix is the only lasting answer.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-dark py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="container text-center max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-warm-white mb-4">Start With the Proposal</h2>
      <p class="text-warm-white/70 text-lg mb-8">
        Read the amendment text. Check the global data. Make up your own mind.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/amendment" class="btn-primary">Read the Amendment</a>
        <a href="/comparison" class="btn-secondary">View Global Comparison</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
